Client :
	- Nickname of a client is 9 characters max (used to distinguish from other clients).

Server:
	- All servers must have the following information about all clients:
		- the real name of the host that the client is running on
		- the username of the client on that host
		- and the server to which the client is connected.

Channels :
	- named group in which clients will all receive messages addressed to that channel.
	- name is 200 characters max.
	- first character has to be '&' or '#'.
	- name cannot contain a space (' '), a control G (^G or ASCII 7), or a comma (',').
	
User :
	- A user may join several channels at once. A limit of 10 is RECOMMENDED.



MODE :
	- When a user join a channel:
		- if the channel doesn't exist, the channel is created and teh user become a channel operator.
		- if the channel exists, whether the user joins is entirely decided by the current modes of the channel. For example if the channel is invite-only (+i), the user may only join if the user is invited.
		
		
